# calculate class distribution
def get_class_distribution(dataset):
    class_counts = {}
    for _, lbl in dataset.unbatch():  # unbatch to iterate over individual samples
        label = lbl.numpy()
        if label in class_counts:
            class_counts[label] += 1
        else:
            class_counts[label] = 1
    return class_counts


train_dist = get_class_distribution(train_dataset)
val_dist = get_class_distribution(validation_dataset)
test_dist = get_class_distribution(test_dataset)

print("Training class distribution:", train_dist)
print("Validation class distribution:", val_dist)
print("Test class distribution:", test_dist)

Validation class distribution: {1: 500, 0: 500}
Test class distribution: {0: 1000, 1: 1000}

  • 1. Define a Neural Network of your choice (3 points)¶

In [215]:
# define a CNN model with 5 layer 
# use functional API
inputs = keras.Input(shape=(180, 180, 3))
x = layers.Rescaling(1./255)(inputs) 
x = layers.Conv2D(32, 3, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D(2)(x)
x = layers.Conv2D(64, 3, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D(2)(x)
x = layers.Conv2D(128, 3, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D(2)(x)
x = layers.Conv2D(256, 3, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D(2)(x)
x = layers.Conv2D(512, 3, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D(2)(x)
x = layers.Flatten()(x) # flatten the output
x = layers.Dense(512, activation='relu')(x) # fully connected layer
x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)  # prevent overfitting
outputs = layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)  # binary classification

model = keras.Model(inputs, outputs)

model.summary()

Model: "functional_23"

# load the vgg16 model
conv_base = keras.applications.vgg16.VGG16(
    weights="imagenet",
    include_top=False,
    input_shape=(180, 180, 3))
conv_base.trainable = False

# build the model with VGG16
inputs = keras.Input(shape=(180, 180, 3))
x = keras.applications.vgg16.preprocess_input(inputs)
x = conv_base(inputs)  
x = layers.Flatten()(x)  
x = layers.Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)  
x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)  
outputs = layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)  

model_vgg16 = keras.Model(inputs, outputs) 
model_vgg16.summary()

In [220]:
def plot_history(history, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], 'bo-', label='Training Accuracy')
    plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], 'b-', label='Validation Accuracy')
    plt.title(f'{title} - Accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.legend()
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(history.history['loss'], 'ro-', label='Training Loss')
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], 'r-', label='Validation Loss')
    plt.title(f'{title} - Loss')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

plot_history(history, 'CNN 5 Layer')
plot_history(history_vgg16, 'VGG16')

# save the images and labels in array, make sure it won't shuffle again
y_true = []
images_test = []
for images, labels in test_dataset:
    y_true.extend(labels.numpy())
    images_test.extend(images.numpy())
images_test = np.array(images_test)
y_true = np.array(y_true)
# get the predictions
y_pred_cnn = best_model_cnn.predict(test_dataset)
y_pred_cnn_classes = (y_pred_cnn > 0.5).astype(int).flatten() # set a threshold
y_pred_vgg = best_model_vgg.predict(test_dataset)
y_pred_vgg_classes = (y_pred_vgg > 0.5).astype(int).flatten() # set a threshold

5. Add your conclusions. (3 point)¶

  • The best_model_with_cnn_5layer model achieves test accuracy approximately 68%.

    • Precision, recall and F1-score hovered around 0.42-0.64 indicating moderate performance.
    • In plot_history part, the growing gap between training and validation performance is a classic overfitting pattern.

  • In contrast, the best_model_with_vgg16 model shows more excelled, although a test accuracy of approximately 74%, but train accuracy reach up to 98% with low loss value, it reflects the VGG16’s ability to capture the cats/dogs features.

    • The confusion matrix shows fewer false positives and false negatives compared to the best_model_with_cnn_5layer, underscoring its stability.
    • The VGG16 model shows more balanced performance across both classes and achieved better overall metrics.
